name: Waves crashing on the beach
description:
Mbawana Beach or Mbawana Beach is located in Kahale Village, Kodi Balaghar District, Sumba Barat Daya SBD), East Nusa Tenggara (NTT) Province, Indonesia.

Bawana Beach or Mbawana Beach has located about 52 km from Tambolaka, the capital of Southwest Sumba Regency. The trip to Mbawana Beach or Mbawana Beach can use two-wheeled or four-wheeled vehicles.

The panorama on Mbawana Beach or Mbawana Beach is amazing. The white sand stretches along the coastline. Even the coral cliffs look firmly standing along Mbawana Beach or Mbawana Beach.

On Mbawana Beach or Mbawana Beach, the waves are also quite large. While you are at Mbawana Beach or Mbawana Beach, you can sunbathe, fish, surf, and dive. But bring some food and drink when visiting Mbawana Beach or Mbawana Beach.

Because on Mbawana Beach or Mbawana Beach there is no accommodation and adequate infrastructure.

But the bad news is, the stone hole on Mbawana beach has been destroyed because it was lashed by the waves around November 2020. So this photo is a witness and evidence of the beauty of Mbawana beach is still intact with perforated rocks.
